// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`buildFrameworkPromptBlock > generates prompt block for GCSE_DT 1`] = `
"
## Curriculum Framework: AQA/OCR GCSE Design & Technology
IMPORTANT: This teacher uses AQA/OCR GCSE Design & Technology, NOT IB MYP. Adjust all terminology:
- Use "assessment objectives" instead of "criteria" (e.g., "AO1" not "A")
- Call the design process the "Iterative Design Process", with phases: Investigate → Design → Make → Evaluate
- Assessment uses: Marks/percentages (NEA 50%, Exam 50%)
- Preferred action verbs: investigate, analyse, evaluate, design, make, test, refine, justify

### Assessment objectives
  - AO1: Identify, investigate and outline design possibilities
  - AO2: Design and make prototypes that are fit for purpose
  - AO3: Analyse and evaluate design decisions and outcomes
  - AO4: Demonstrate and apply knowledge and understanding
  - AO5: Core technical principles (written exam)

### Notes
Non-Examined Assessment (NEA) is the coursework portfolio. Core technical principles tested in written exam. Focus on new and emerging technologies, sustainability, materials properties.

Do NOT use MYP-specific terms like "Statement of Inquiry", "Global Context", "ATL Skills", "criterion A-D", or "achievement levels 1-8" unless this IS an MYP unit.
"
`;
